text: Happy New Year! Wishing everybody in Queens and across the nation a healthy, prosperous and joyous 2018.
To all who celebrate #Kwanzaa, I wish you and your family a very happy holiday.
Sending my warmest wishes for a very Merry #Christmas to everybody celebrating here in Queens and throughout the nation.

Sad about the passing of #SanFrancisco Mayor Ed Lee. Mayor Lee was a dedicated public servant who worked tirelessly for the residents of San Francisco. An advocate for housing & civil rights issues, he broke barriers to become San Francisco’s first Asian American mayor. 1/2

I voted against legislation that would allow concealed weapons to be carried across state lines. As mass shootings become more frequent & more deadly, Congress should be working to reduce gun violence, NOT unleashing even more guns on our streets & putting our safety at risk.

No matter the work environment, no employee should face sexual harassment. That’s why I voted to require sexual harassment training for all Members of Congress & their staffs, fellows, & interns, a policy that already exists in my own office. This is only the first step forward.

Deeply troubled over the FCC’s plan to repeal #NetNeutrality rules. RT if you believe that our Internet should be OPEN AND FREE!
